    "what_description": "Allantodia crinipes is a species of fern in the family Aspleniaceae. It is a perennial herb with a slender rhizome and erect or spreading fronds, typically 20-50 cm tall, with a lanceolate to ovate rachis and ovate-lanceolate to linear-lanceolate pinnae. The pinnae are usually 2-4 pairs, with the proximal pinnae the largest and most ovate, and the distal pinnae gradually smaller and more linear. The fronds are usually dark green above and lighter below, with a smooth or slightly serrate margin. The plant reproduces via spores produced on the underside of the fronds, in the sori, which are usually rounded and paraphyllous.",
