    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Allantodia crinipes are flavonoids, including quercetin and kaempferol, which possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties; terpenoids, such as ursolic and oleanolic acid, which exhibit anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities; and phenolic acids, including ferulic and sinapic acid, which have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects. These constituents have been shown to contribute to the plant's ability to reduce inflammation and oxidative stress, which may help to explain its traditional use in treating various health conditions. Research has demonstrated that quercetin can inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes, while kaempferol has been shown to have anti-cancer properties. The terpenoids present in Allantodia crinipes have been found to have antimicrobial activity against a range of bacteria and fungi. Overall, the combination of flavonoids, terpenoids, and phenolic acids in Allantodia crinipes may contribute to its potential therapeutic benefits.",
